                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14466815" author="blackdrag" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2009 12:22:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;another problem was that LocalMap was referenced strong by the ThreadLocal. In a system with a thread pool, that means that this data will never be collected, since the thread won&apos;t be collected. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466878" author="blackdrag" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2009 12:24:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the latest attempt to fix that will now SoftReference the LocalMap, that should avoid the memory problem. Also the ThreadLocal itself is available per WeakReference only, so theoretically the ThreadLocal can be collected now. Of course the Thread is having a strong reference to it, so I doubt this will actually happen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
